[MESSAGE]I'm going to talk to you about the nuances of a second floor. Having a second floor means you can pack in roughly double the number of customers. It also means the time it takes to deliver the food all the way up from the kitchen takes roughly twice as long - and nothing risks annoying a customer more than a warm dish served cold!

We will look into minimizing the delivery time. _Left-click_ on the restaurant's kitchen floor to continue.
[POSITION]475,50
[DIMENSION]400,250
[HINT]

[MESSAGE]Now _left-click_ on the _Interior Panel_. Notice how the _Interior Panel_ now only shows kitchen-related items? The _Interior Panel_ will only show you items relevant to each room. Your kitchen comes stocked with most everything you will need, but there are some missing items that you will need to fully equip your kitchen. One of these is the _dumb waiter_.

Find the _dumb waiter_ among the kitchen item thumbnails and add it along an available empty space, then _left-click_ on the _Next_ button to continue.
[POSITION]475,50
[DIMENSION]400,250
[HINT]446,415,496,471

[MESSAGE]Good! Since we're in the kitchen, take some time to examine the kitchen facilities available in the _interior panel_ that you will work with during your career as a chef, and read each facility's description.
[POSITION]475,32
[DIMENSION]310,250
[HINT]

[MESSAGE]Pay special attention to the _Waiting Station_. Every restaurant needs at least one in the kitchen. Since the _Waiting Station_ is where your waitstaff pick up food for delivery, failure to place one means no food will be delivered! Treize ŕ table already has one in the kitchen, so no need to add one here. However, make sure you place a _Waiting Station_ in any kitchen that you set up in the future!

_Left-click_ on the _Next_ button to continue.
[POSITION]475,50
[DIMENSION]400,250
[HINT]

[MESSAGE]Now, go upstairs by _left-clicking_ on the _up/down floor_ button.
[POSITION]475,50
[DIMENSION]400,250
[HINT]

[MESSAGE]Look for the upstairs shaft of the _dumb waiter_. Whenever a customer is dining upstairs, this is where food will be delivered to from the kitchen downstairs . Installing a dumb waiter is useful, as it usually shaves 50% off the total delivery time.

Now we will look into some additional features found under the _item interface_. First, open the _interior panel_ if you haven't already done so.
[POSITION]475,50
[DIMENSION]400,250
[HINT]

[MESSAGE]Now _left-click_ on the _seating arrangements_ button. This will show the available _small table sets_ seating arrangements when you first open it.
[POSITION]475,50
[DIMENSION]400,250
[HINT]373,386,407,409

[MESSAGE]You are looking at the available chair and table combinations available for this restaurant type. The highlighted button shows two-seat table sets, complete with a comfort attribute, description and pricing. Let's add a few sets. Adding table sets is similar to adding floor-placed decorations - you remember from our first lesson, right?

When you are done adding chair and table sets _left-click_ on the _Next_ button to continue.
[POSITION]475,50
[DIMENSION]400,250
[HINT]373,386,407,409

[MESSAGE]Four-seat tables are also available, useful for larger groups of customers. _Left-click_ on the _large table sets_ subcategory. You will see the available options. Choose a set and add a few on the floor, although it is better to add the same chair/table combination to provide some consistency to your layout.

When you are done adding large chair sets, _left-click_ on the _Next_ button to continue.
[POSITION]445,60
[DIMENSION]430,250
[HINT]373,386,407,409

[MESSAGE]By the way, if you haven't noticed, some items, especially the table sets and the kitchen facilities, have a blue bounding box as well as green ones. Customers and staff occupy the blue area of items to interact with them. Don't block these areas, or else your staff will be unable to make use of kitchen facilities, and customers won't be able to sit down to enjoy a meal!

Here's a rule of thumb: if you cannot place an item in your restaurant, simply look at the help message displayed on the top of the screen. It will tell you why you can't place it.

When you are done filling the room with seats, chairs and decoration, _left-click_ on the _recipe menu_ button to continue.
[POSITION]445,60
[DIMENSION]400,250
[HINT]407,386,438,408

[MESSAGE]Flip through some recipes, and pay attention to the _requires_ field. See how the icons change with each recipe? If you see an icon it means you need that kitchen facility in order to make that recipe. If it's over a green background, it means you already possess that item in your kitchen; over a red background, it means you need to add that item before you can prepare that particular recipe.

_Left-click_ on the _next_ button to continue.
[POSITION]475,50
[DIMENSION]400,250
[HINT]91,383,197,427

[MESSAGE]Look up the _Crepes Marcie_ recipe. It's under _Desserts_. You will notice that this recipe requires a _food processor_ for its preparation. If you plan on offering this succulent dish, you will need to add the _food processor_ in order to prepare this recipe, or else chefs will not have the necessary facilities to render the recipe. Different recipes have different facility requirements, so be sure that you have the necessary items in place!

Now go downstairs. There's more I have to show you.
[POSITION]475,50
[DIMENSION]400,250
[HINT]

[MESSAGE]_Left-click_ on the restaurant's kitchen floor. The _food processor_ has to be placed on a _preparation table_, so go ahead and place it. _Microwave ovens_ are also placed on the _preparation table_.

When you are done placing the necessary items in your kitchen, _left-click_ on the _recipe menu_ button to continue.
[POSITION]475,50
[DIMENSION]400,250
[HINT]

[MESSAGE]Let's take a look at how you can change a recipe's overall quality. Notice the _Essential Ingredients_ column? These are the default settings for each recipe. All recipes come with a three-star ingredient quality, the maximum quality rating for _Essential Ingredients_. You can adjust an ingredient's quality if you first _mouse over_ the stars of the ingredient you want to adjust. You will notice a gray box outlining the stars, along with _left_ and _right arrow_ buttons. If you click on these, you can adjust the ingredients to a higher or lower quality.

When you are done adjusting, _left-click_ on the _Next_ button to continue.
[POSITION]180,340
[DIMENSION]600,400
[HINT]360,98,701,289

[MESSAGE]You must be wondering at the purpose of demoting a recipe's quality. First, your restaurant may not have a very high rating. If you prepare top-notch food in an average restaurant, customers will not expect to pay so much for their meals. That will cause many an irate customer! Likewise, if you have a very high restaurant rating, customers will be irked by the restaurant's poor food quality.

The secret is in balancing your recipe quality with the restaurant's rating, so why don't you try this now? Adjust a recipe's quality so that it has a one-point-five-star recipe rating.
[POSITION]368,320
[DIMENSION]430,400
[HINT]360,98,701,289

[MESSAGE]The more restaurants you have catering to different customer budgets, the more you will need to fine-tune a recipe's quality. All this fine-tuning can get out of hand quickly - that's why there is the _Duplicate Recipe_ button. When you are done fine-tuning a recipe, _left-click_ on the _Duplicate Recipe_ button. A popup message will appear indicating that the recipe has been duplicated. Don't forget to adjust the recipe's _Menu Price_ to suit the new rating!

After you have duplicated a recipe, _left-click_ on the _Next_ button to continue.
[POSITION]550,32
[DIMENSION]240,200
[HINT]206,458,242,494

[MESSAGE]Excellent! You now know how to save food delivery time as well as different recipe requirements and the usage of different kitchen items. And not only do you know how to change a recipe's ingredient quality, you also know how to setup floor layouts. What's most important is now you have a restaurant that is fully utilized. Congratulations - you've come a long way!

Before I leave you on your own, I want to remind you that _your goal is to reach a monthly revenue of $40,000 and 50% of your meals have to be served on time. You have three months_ to accomplish these goals. Good luck!
